Rivatex East Africa Managing Director Thomas Kipkurgat said that the textile firm will use the event to market their products.Kipkurgat revealed that plans were underway to revive Rivatex Football Club that once featured in Kenya’s top football league. Eldoret Golf Club will host a charity tournament to raise funds for former servicemen and women injured in the line of duty.
The inaugural Leletsa Fashion for Heroes golf challenge, which has attracted more than 80 players golfers, will tee off at 7:30am Saturday.
Leletsa Fashion Chief Executive Officer Naftali Korir said that the tournament will celebrate former members of the disciplined forces through fashion with focus on Kenyan designs. The company was formed in June this year.



